      • align

        public static List<Tuple<Integer,Integer>> align(List<Triple<Long,Long,Double>> left,
                                                 List<Triple<Long,Long,Double>> right)
        Gets optimal alignment of two paths, e.g. map matching results, which are given as sequences of edges with source id, target id and length of an edge.
        Parameters:
        left - One sequence of edges with source id, target id, and length in meters.
        right - Other sequence of edges with source id, target id, and length in meters.
        Returns:
        Optimal alignment of two sequences of edges, which is a sequence of tuples referring to matching edges of the input sequences.

      • candidatesToSequence

        public static List<Triple<Long,Long,Double>> candidatesToSequence(List<MatcherCandidate> candidates)
        Converts map matching results, which is sequence of matcher candidates, to a sequence of edges given as source id, target id and length in meters.
        Parameters:
        candidates - Map matching results, which is sequence of matcher candidates.
        Returns:
        Sequence of edges defined by source id, target id and length in meters.

      • error

        public static double error(List<Triple<Long,Long,Double>> left,
                           List<Triple<Long,Long,Double>> right,
                           List<Tuple<Integer,Integer>> alginment)
        Calculates error of path alignment of two sequences of edges defined by source id, target id and length in meters.
        Parameters:
        left - One sequence of edges with source id, target id, and length in meters.
        right - Other sequence of edges with source id, target id, and length in meters.
        alginment - Alignment of two sequences of edges, which is a sequence of tuples referring to matching edges of the input sequences.
        Returns:
        Error value that sums length of all non matched edges of input paths.
